00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.802
What is NodeJS?

2
00:00:01.802 --> 00:00:06.045
Well, NodeJS is JavaScript kind
of like what I said before, but

3
00:00:06.045 --> 00:00:09.991
more specifically it's a run
time built on Chrome's V8.

4
00:00:09.991 --> 00:00:14.404
So if you've never heard of Chrome's V8
it's the engine that sits inside of Chrome

5
00:00:14.404 --> 00:00:17.701
that actually compiles your
JavaScript down to machine code so

6
00:00:17.701 --> 00:00:21.678
it can be processed, because JavaScript
actually has to be interpreted and

7
00:00:21.678 --> 00:00:23.005
execute it on a machine.

8
00:00:23.005 --> 00:00:24.543
V8 is the engine that does that.

9
00:00:24.543 --> 00:00:29.060
So some really smart person decided
to strip V8 out of Chrome and

10
00:00:29.060 --> 00:00:30.660
stick it on a machine.

11
00:00:30.660 --> 00:00:34.995
And that allows you to run node, and
that's basically what we have here.

12
00:00:34.995 --> 00:00:37.240
And everything is built on top of that.

13
00:00:37.240 --> 00:00:42.451
So just like on the front end, JavaScript
and node is also gonna be based off

14
00:00:42.451 --> 00:00:47.664
an event loop, which if you don't
really know what that means, we'll get

15
00:00:47.664 --> 00:00:52.990
into that a little more but just know
is that JavaScript is single threaded.

16
00:00:52.990 --> 00:00:56.861
As in it's only going to
be able to process work and

17
00:00:56.861 --> 00:01:01.022
amount of work in like one
little isolated instance.

18
00:01:01.022 --> 00:01:03.595
And then everything else kind
of runs in the background.

19
00:01:03.595 --> 00:01:08.425
This allows node to be able to process
things much faster than a lot of

20
00:01:08.425 --> 00:01:13.357
other OSS level languages,
as long as those tasks are not CPU bound.

21
00:01:13.357 --> 00:01:16.442
So if you're not doing things
like arithmetic or AI, or

22
00:01:16.442 --> 00:01:19.464
machine learning node js is
probably a perfect tool for

23
00:01:19.464 --> 00:01:23.076
